additionalInformation:
An outcome describes a future state which is different than the current state. An outcome is different from an output. In a results chain, outcomes are located after outupts and before impacts. Business plans, programmes and policies all include outcomes.
After the programme activities have been implemented:
outcomes (changes which occurred as a result of the programme activities being implemented) are measured using indicators. Outcomes may be short termed, intermediate termed or long termed. Short-term outcomes of educational programs may include changes in:
Awareness–People recognize the problem or issue;
knowledge– People understand the causes and potential solutions;
Skills–People possess the skills needed to resolve the situation;
Motivation–People have the desire to effect change;
Attitude–People believe their actions can make a difference.
Intermediate-term outcomes include changes that follow the short-term outcomes, such as changes in:
Practices used by participants;
Behaviors exhibited by people or organizations;
Policies adopted by governments,or organizations;
Technologies employed by end users;
Management strategies implemented by individuals or groups.
